snippet.textDisplay:
I'm kinda tired with all this shitty AMD fanboying, your comparing a apple to a orange. These cpus are for 2 demographics, ones cheaper for poorer people while the other one is more expensive with better performance for people who can cash that money out. Just because you have AMD doesnt make you better. And the security flaws wont even be a problem if you dont mess with anything suspicious. C'mon guys you dont need to feel in top just because you use an AMD.

Edit: on top of the security, AMD is very vulnerable as well. Thing is less people use AMD chips, this means hackers will usually target a bigger group like Intel. This has been seen before like windows to mac. You may have your own security vulnerabilities one day.
I have nothing against AMD, they make their fair share of good cpus, but the community is intoxicating the company.

snippet.textDisplay:
Everyone talks about Mac and Chrome OS being "impossible to hack and infect with viruses." What about Linux? Show Linux some love. You literally can't infect a linux distro with a virus unless you're either 
A) a total dumbass
B) old and have no clue what you're doing
or C) trying to infect the computer intentionally. 

I can't speak for the hacking resistance, but I suspect it's just as secure. Unless you intentionally disable it through the command line, which I and I'm sure others don't even know how to do,  your user password is required for EVERYTHING you install or modify on the OS. Fight me, Linux is more secure than Mac.
